The Royal Danish Navy has named several ships after him, including an early 20th century coastal defence ship. The Niels Juel class corvette KDM Peter Tordenskiold (F356), served from around 1980 to August 2009.Korvetter af NIELS JUEL-klassen at Royal Danish Navy The Royal Norwegian Navy has also named ships after him, such as the coastal defence ship Tordenskjold, and the Royal Norwegian Naval Training Establishment in Bergen is named KNM Tordenskjold.